Bug 2048162 - Fix new mail alert appearing on wrong monitor with mixed-DPI setups. r=mkmelin

The fix for bug 2034322 cached the alert window's own `screen` metrics to
prevent monitor bleed during layout, but this fails on mixed-DPI setups
where the OS may place the popup on the wrong monitor from the start.

Instead, capture the main Thunderbird window's screen geometry and pass it
to the alert, so `snapToCorner()` always targets the correct monitor. Falls
back to the alert's own `screen` when the main window isn't available.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D307908

diff --git a/mailnews/base/content/newmailalert.js b/mailnews/base/content/newmailalert.js
